).parse(parser, bean);\n        parser.parse(args);\n    }\n}\n</pre></code>\n\n<p>While the <code>FieldParser</code> is easier to use, the <code>XmlParser</code> supports more features.</p>\n<p>That said, it supports all features which are available via annotations: usage text, specifying handlers, and more. You have to provide an XML <code>InputSource</code> or a URL to the XML file.</p>\n\n<p>This feature is available since Args4J release 2.0.16:</p>\n\n<code><pre>\npublic class Bean {\n    String text;\n\n[16 more lines in file. Use offset=85 to continue.]"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777670483619}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_KJcKeuffEtdjzBzTqJNzcLHJ|fc_0d99e4f49ed2862c0169f519536a8081a38a6b05af4bb658c9", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"classes\" : [ {\n    \"callSites\" : [ {\n      \"covered\" : false,\n      \"frame\" : \"org.kohsuke.args4j.FieldParser.parse(FieldParser.java:19)\",\n      \"line\" : 19,\n      \"metadataType\" : \"reflection\",\n      \"trackedApi\" : \"java.lang.Class#getDeclaredFields()\"\n    } ],\n    \"className\" : \"org.kohsuke.args4j.FieldParser\",\n    \"coveredCalls\" : 0,\n    \"sourceFile\" : \"FieldParser.java\",\n    \"totalCalls\" : 1\n  }, {\n    \"callSites\" : [ {\n      \"covered\" : false,\n      \"frame\" : \"org.kohsuke.args4j.Messages.format(Messages.java:30)\",\n      \"line\" : 30,\n      \"metadataType\" : \"resources\",\n      \"trackedApi\" : \"java.util.ResourceBundle#getBundle(java.lang.String)\"\n    } ],\n    \"className\" : \"org.kohsuke.args4j.Messages\",\n    \"coveredCalls\" : 0,\n    \"sourceFile\" : \"Messages.java\",\n    \"totalCalls\" : 1\n  }, {\n    \"callSites\" : [ {\n      \"covered\" : false,\n      \"frame\" : \"org.kohsuke.args4j.spi.AnnotationImpl.<init>(AnnotationImpl.java:22)\",\n      \"line\" : 22,\n      \"metadataType\" : \"reflection\",\n      \"trackedApi\" : \"java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)\"\n    } ],\n    \"className